     <div type="argument">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <list>
      <head>The Text diuided.</head>
      <item>Blessed is he that conside<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>reth the poor, The Lorde will deliuer him in the time of his trouble. Psal. <hi>41.1.</hi>
         <list>
            <item>
               <hi>1.</hi> The de<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>scription of a good man. In these wordes, Bles<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sed is hee, that, &amp;c.
<list>
                  <item>
                     <hi>1.</hi> The title ascribed to such a person, That he is blessed.</item>
                  <item>
                     <hi>2.</hi> The mani<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>fest marke of such a man: That he consi<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>dereth of the poore.</item>
               </list>
            </item>
            <item>
               <hi>2.</hi> The be<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>nefite belong<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ing to such a person: The Lorde will deliuer him, &amp;c.
<list>
                  <item>
                     <hi>1.</hi> His safe pre<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>seruation, in these words: The Lorde will deliuer him.</item>
                  <item>
                     <hi>2.</hi> The time when, especially, In the time of his trouble.</item>
               </list>
            </item>
         </list>
      </item>
   </list>
   <p>In the handling of which points, verie profitable instructions will appeare concerning the poor, how they may bee relieued this deare yeare in all places, without surcharging any person.</p>
